[[Nine Inch Nails]] is an [[United States|American]] [[industrial rock]] act, founded in 1988 by [[Trent Reznor]] in [[Cleveland, Ohio|Cleveland]], [[Ohio]].  As its main [[Record producer|producer]], singer, songwriter, and instrumentalist, Reznor is the only official member of Nine Inch Nails and remains solely responsible for its direction.<ref name="AMG">{{cite web |author= Huey, Steve |url= http://wm04.allmusic.com/cg/amg.dll?p=amg&sql=11:jxkcikv6bbf9~T10 |title= Nine Inch Nails |accessdate= 2006-11-24 |publisher= [[Allmusic]]}}</ref>  Nine Inch Nails has received four awards from 25 nominations, including two [[Grammy Award]]s for the songs "[[Wish (song)|Wish]]" and "[[Happiness in Slavery]]" in 1993 and 1996 respectively.<ref name="LA Times">{{cite web
  | url = http://theenvelope.latimes.com/factsheets/awardsdb/env-awards-db-search,0,7169155.htmlstory?searchtype=person&query=nine+inch+nails&x=0&y=0
  | title = Awards Database
  | publisher = ''Los Angeles Times''
  | accessdate = 2007-11-10}}</ref>  Nine Inch Nails have received two [[Kerrang! Awards|''Kerrang!'' Awards]] honoring the band's overall contributions since 1988.<ref name="Kerrang songwriter">{{cite web
  | url = http://www.guardian.co.uk/media/2005/aug/26/pressandpublishing
  | publisher = ''[[The Guardian]]''
  | title = Green Day triumph at Kerrang! awards
  | date = [[2005-08-26]]
  | last = Jones
  | first = Sam
  | accessdate = 2008-08-31}}</ref><ref name="Kerrang icon">{{cite web
  | url = http://www.guardian.co.uk/media/2005/aug/26/pressandpublishing
  | publisher = [[bbc.co.uk]]
  | title = Brit bands rock Kerrang! awards
  | date = [[2007-08-24]]
  | accessdate = 2008-08-31}}</ref>  The band has also received nine nominations from the [[MTV Video Music Awards]] for several of its videos, including two nominations for the "[[Closer (Nine Inch Nails song)|Closer]]" video and five nominations for the "[[The Perfect Drug|Perfect Drug]]" video, including [[MTV Video Music Award for Video of the Year|Video of the Year]].<ref name="LA Times" />

Nine Inch Nails and several of its releases have also received awards and honors from the critical community.  The band was ranked as the 94th "Greatest Artist of All Time" by ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' in 2004.<ref name="RS100">{{cite web
  | url = http://www.rollingstone.com/artists/nineinchnails/articles/story/7250012/the_immortals__the_greatest_artists_of_all_time_94_nine_inch_nails
  | first = David
  | last = Bowie
  | authorlink = David Bowie
  | title = The Immortals - The Greatest Artists of All Time: 94) Nine Inch Nails 
  | publisher = ''[[Rolling Stone]]''
  | date = [[2005-04-22]]
  | accessdate = 2008-01-10}}</ref>  Nine Inch Nails' second studio album, ''[[The Downward Spiral]]'', has been included on several "Best Of" lists, including ''Rolling Stone''<nowiki>'s</nowiki> "[[Rolling Stone's 500 Greatest Albums of All Time|500 Greatest Albums of All Time]]" and ''[[Spin (magazine)|Spin]]''<nowiki>'s</nowiki> "100 Greatest Albums, 1985<U+2013>2005".<ref name="RS500">{{cite web
  | url = http://www.rollingstone.com/news/story/5938174/the_rs_500_greatest_albums_of_all_time/2
  | title = RS 500 Greatest Albums of All Time
  | publisher = ''Rolling Stone''
  | date = [[2003-11-18]]
  | accessdate = 2008-07-31}}</ref><ref name="Spin100">{{cite journal
  | journal = [[Spin (magazine)|Spin]]
  | title = 100 Greatest Albums, 1985-2005
  | issue = July 2005}}</ref>

==American Music Awards==
The [[American Music Award]]s are awarded annually by a poll of music buyers. Nine Inch Nails has received two nominations.  

{{awards table}}
|-
| align="center"| 1994
| Nine Inch Nails
| Favorite Alternative Artist
| {{nom}}
|-
| align="center"| 1995
| Nine Inch Nails
| Favorite Alternative Artist
| {{nom}}
{{end}}

==Billboard Awards==
=== Billboard Music Awards ===
The [[Billboard Music Award]]s are sponsored by ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' magazine and is held annually in December.  Nine Inch Nails has received one nomination.

{{awards table}}
|-
| align="center"| 2005
| Nine Inch Nails
| Modern Rock Artist of the Year
| {{nom}}
{{end}}

=== Billboard Music Video Awards ===
The Billboard Music Video Awards are sponsored by ''Billboard'' magazine. Nine Inch Nails has received one nomination.

{{awards table}}
|-
| align="center"| 2000
| "[[Starfuckers, Inc.]]"
| Best Modern Rock Clip of the Year
| {{nom}}
|-
{{end}}

==Grammy Awards==
The [[Grammy Award]]s are awarded annually by the [[National Academy of Recording Arts and Sciences]]. Nine Inch Nails has received two awards from ten nominations.

